headline: Keysight and Capgemini Accelerate Validation of Regenerative and Transparent Non-Terrestrial Network RAN
summary: SANTA ROSA, Calif., March 05, 2025--Keysight Technologies, Inc. (NYSE: KEYS) is collaborating with Capgemini to integrate and validate 5G new radio (NR) non-terrestrial networks (NTN) in both transparent and regenerative modes. This collaboration aims to accelerate Capgemini’s development of its 5G NR NTN ready radio access network (RAN) framework. A demonstration of this achievement will be showcased at Keysight’s booth (#5F41 Hall 5) and Capgemini’s booth (#2K21 Hall 2) during Mobile World Con

headline: Keysight Chosen to Validate Performance, Security, and Resilience of U.S. Army’s Unified Network at Cyber Quest ‘25
summary: SANTA ROSA, Calif., March 05, 2025--Keysight Technologies, Inc. (NYSE: KEYS) announces that the United States Army has selected Keysight’s CyPerf network design and verification solution to validate performance, resiliency, and zero trust security for their Unified Network Program during Cyber Quest ’25 (CQ25).

content.title: Keysight Chosen to Validate Performance, Security, and Resilience of U.S. Army’s Unified Network at Cyber Quest ‘25

thumbnail.caption: Keysight CyPerf, an instantly scalable zero trust test solution, delivers unprecedented insights into end-user experience, security posture, and performance bottlenecks. (Photo: Business Wire)
